# Movie Finder Docs — Cursor Rules

This file is a legacy fallback. Cursor loads the richer MDC rules from `.cursor/rules/` automatically.

If your IDE supports MDC rules, the following files apply:
- `.cursor/rules/project.mdc` — always active (docs context, rendering commands)
- `.cursor/rules/architect.mdc` — activates on `.puml`, `workspace.dsl`, `decisions/`
- `.cursor/rules/developer.mdc` — activates when implementing doc issues

---

## Quick reference

**Repo:** `aharbii/movie-finder-docs` · Primary context: `CLAUDE.md`

**Non-negotiables:**
- Never generate `.mdj` StarUML files — user converts `.puml` to StarUML manually
- Edit `.puml` source only — PNGs are generated at build time and gitignored
- `make mkdocs` must run clean before any PR
- ADR required for every new tech decision or project-wide pattern change
- Conventional Commits: `docs(architecture): summary`
- Disclose AI tool + model in every PR
